Key Match Events: Immanuel Quickley scored a 29-foot three-pointer to cap a 25-6 Raptors run in the fourth quarter
Post-Match Reflections: Immanuel Quickley expressed gratitude for being able to compete after missing the Raptors' last 22 games with a partially torn ulnar collateral ligament in his right elbow
Others: Toronto Raptors snapped an 11-game losing skid with the win over Brooklyn Nets
